## Conclusion

This refactoring successfully centralizes the event handling infrastructure into a reusable, well-designed module that:

1. Reduces code duplication across services
2. Provides a clean, type-safe API for event handling
3. Uses efficient hash-based handler lookup
4. Maintains thread safety and proper resource management
5. Integrates seamlessly with the existing HoloCanvas error handling framework
6. Requires minimal changes to service business logic

The services retain their domain-specific handler implementations while delegating all Kafka infrastructure concerns to the shared event dispatcher module.

